      {
        "type": "email",
        "html": "<p>Hello {first_name, \"there\"},</p><p>I've been thinking a lot about where to take this site next year, and as I noodle with ideas and read around, I'm beginning to see three themes emerging:</p><ul><li>Trust ‚Äî rebuilding public faith in journalism</li><li>Tech ‚Äî making better use of the emerging tools to do better journalism</li><li>Technique ‚Äî rethinking <em>how</em> we do journalism</li></ul><p>All three are clearly and deeply interlinked, but they feel like the conversations we <em>need</em> to be having right now.</p><p>I'd be interested to hear what you think ‚Äî about the idea, or about the categories. And tomorrow's piece will be all about trust. It was actually today's intro, but it got a little out of hand, and one cut-and-paste later, it's ready to be further developed for your reading delight.</p><p>But at least two of the links below are to do with trust, so let's get on with it‚Ä¶</p>"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "When the BMJ and the HSJ hit the front pages",
